13/01/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling Socialist Party (SP) is likely to postpone its party congress -- initially scheduled for 29 January -- until April, given ongoing electoral reforms. At the request of Prime Minister and SP leader Fatos Nano, the party's presidency met on Thursday (13 January) to discuss the possible postponement. An official decision is expected by the end of the week. (Albanian News - 13/01/05)
